item.title: News
item.description: Day #1 A new scholar year, a new “Romanian Master of Informatics” edition, the sixth, hosted by the “Tudor Vianu” High School of Computer Science started today, October the 10th 2018. The Romanian contestants were joined by students from Bulgaria, Italy, Moldova, Poland, Russia, Serbia and Greece. They were welcomed in the events hall, where students Anca Ghinea and Rareș Ionescu presented the competing teams and the artistic moments.
